Yes â€” âœ… running a background job on sd-wv58-kflz.nam.nsroot.net to load, tag, and push all Docker images from /docker2/*/images is a very good idea â€” especially since:

Youâ€™re not using internet access.

You have a lot of .tar.gz images to load and push.

